DocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104omd1665703132326.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/omd1665703132326.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/omd1665703132326.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"omd1665703132326\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"omd1665703132326__ufputext_402796\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field, allowing the data to exceed the field length.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"omd1665703132326__topic_d119870e1_d119871e1_d119872e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104omd1665703132326_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"omd1665703132326__codeblock_k3z_prz_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short ufputext (unsigned char* field, unsigned char* buffer, short length);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"omd1665703132326__topic_d85322e1_d85323e1_d85324e1_d85325e1_d85326e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1151044e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"omd1665703132326__parml_qtn_srz_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the\n                  field name with an entity name, for example, <var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity</var>. Instead of the actual field name, you also use the\n                  internal bind name as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetbind</code>.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Data to be copied to the field. This data does not have to be\n                  zero-terminated.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">length</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Number of bytes that should be copied from <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var> to\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var>. Use a negative value to indicate that more data is to\n                  follow (using additional calls to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code>).</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"omd1665703132326__topic_d85327e1_d85328e1_d85329e1_d85330e1_d85331e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1151044e121\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ufput, ufputi, ufputc, and ufputext</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__2\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__1\">-1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__2\">An error occurred.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__1\">0 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__2\">All data was copied to the field .</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__1\">1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"omd1665703132326__d6834e20__entry__2\">There is more data to be copied to the field.\n                        Occurs when you have specified a negative <var class=\"keyword varname\">Length</var>\n                        value.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"omd1665703132326__topic_d85337e1_d85338e1_d85339e1_d85340e1_d85341e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1151044e185\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"omd1665703132326__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"omd1665703132326__topic_d85342e1_d85343e1_d85344e1_d85345e1_d85346e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1151044e198\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"omd1665703132326__p_d119909e1_d119910e1_d119911e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputext</code> treats the data as RAW. It is largely equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code>, but it is possible for the data to exceed the field length. However, if the field data will be stored, exceeding the field length will lead to a store error later on.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"omd1665703132326__note_N100A2_N1008D_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ufputext</span>\n            should NOT be used in conjunction with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ufputc</span>.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyq1665703132133.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufput</a><p>Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhm1665703132396.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufputc</a><p>Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dxp1665703132477.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufputi</a><p>Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field as if the switch /init were used.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ene1665703131995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetbind</a><p>Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530646\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530646\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ufputext Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field, allowing the data to exceed the field length. Explain this code short ufputext (unsigned char* field, unsigned char* buffer, short length); Copy Parameters field Name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the field name with an entity name, for example, field . entity . Instead of the actual field name, you also use the internal bind name as returned by ugetbind . buffer Data to be copied to the field. This data does not have to be zero-terminated. length Number of bytes that should be copied from buffer to field . Use a negative value to indicate that more data is to follow (using additional calls to ufputc ). Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ufput, ufputi, ufputc, and ufputext Value Meaning -1 An error occurred. 0 All data was copied to the field . 1 There is more data to be copied to the field. Occurs when you have specified a negative Length value. Use Library: yrtl Description ufputext treats the data as RAW. It is largely equivalent to ufput , but it is possible for the data to exceed the field length. However, if the field data will be stored, exceeding the field length will lead to a store error later on. CAUTION: ufputext should NOT be used in conjunction with ufputc . Related Links ufput Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. ufputc Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. ufputi Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field as if the switch /init were used. ugetbind Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}